RACE.RACE_TEXT: Joe Hernandez S. - Grade2 SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Turf CR: 110. Stakes Purse 200000. DOWNHILL TURF FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, December 21, 2023, closed with 22 or by Supplementary nomination of $4,000 due at time of entry. $1,500 to enter and an additional $1,500 to start wi th $200,000 guaranteed of which $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth, and $4,000 to fifth. Three-Year-Olds 123 lbs. Older 125 lbs. Non-Winners of a Grade I or Grade II Stake since June 30, 2023 allowed 2 lbs. Non- Winners of Graded Stakes since December 30, 2022 allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORBIDDEN KINGDOM stepped to the front and set the pace in hand while under pressure from DANCING BUCK, headed by that rival on the turn, inched ahead in upper stretch, maintained a short lead into deep stretch and held gamely. DANCING BUCK broke well and prompted the pace from outside, headed FORBIDDEN KINGDOM on the turn, kept the pressure on through the lane and could not summon the needed late kick to get by the winner. TURN ON THE JETS (IRE) broke alertly then took a stalking position outside a rival, rounded the bend in the two path, chased within striking distance through the final furlong but lacked the needed late response while holding third. DANIEL'S MAGIC also broke alertly and moved inside stalking the top pair, saved ground through the turn, roused leaving the bend and finished evenly along the fence. I'M A GAMBLER (IRE) chased in the two path and could not produce a bid when called upon. BALNIKHOV (IRE) broke a step slow, traveled near the back outside a rival then between foes, took the turn two wide, kept to task in the final furlong and improved position. LUCKY SCORE located towards the rear early on the inside, ran into traffic briefly at the quarter pole, angled out in the lane and offered a mild rally. TAHOE SUNRISE raced in range early outside rivals, coaxed along three wide on the bend, put to left handed urging with a furlong remaining but weakened in the late stages. JOHNNY PODRES tracked three deep early, spun four wide into the lane, moved out in the lane and failed to threaten. FRONT RUN THE FED broke a step slow, trailed early then went outside rivals, rounded the bend three deep, found traffic in the lane and could not threaten. OLYMPIC RUNNER settled four deep, navigated the turn five wide, bothered by JOHNNY PODRES at the eighth pole and failed to menace. PEACEFUL WATERS broke a step slow, chased keenly early when rating inside out of range, saved ground through the turn, weakened in the drive, eased in deep stretch and walked off. Due to a timing malfunction, the three-quarter fractional time on video is incorrect.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND TIGER dueled inside THE GIANTS CANDY into and around the turn, inched ahead in upper stretch and held gamely to the wire. THE GIANTS CANDY dueled outside GRAND TIGER, kept the pressure on through the lane and finished gamely in defeat. MONGOLIAN GOLD broke a step slow and dropped back early, trailed two wide leaving the backstretch, moved to the rail to save ground, came with a late run along the fence and gained third. KING ZOG chased the top pair on the inside into the turn, moved out and loomed three wide into the lane and lacked the needed late kick in the furlong grounds. BLUEGRASS RYDER lacked early speed despite being coaxed along, traveled along the rail then angled out and came four wide into the drive and failed to threaten. VENOM chased in range for a bit then started to lose ground leaving the backstretch, dropped back to last while three wide on the turn and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANGEL NADESHIKO established the front and crossed to the inside, controlled the pace through the early going, met the bid from REBEL GIRL on the far turn, roused exiting the bend and put that rival away at the top of the stretch, asked right handed midstretch and held well. LAKOTA SPIRIT stalked along the rail, cut the corner into the stretch, chased within striking range under right handed urging but could only whittle the gap on the winner late. OAKHURST settled in the two path, ridden along on the second bend, moved out in the drive and edged YERWANTHERE (IRE) for the show honors. YERWANTHERE (IRE) trailed two wide then moved inside on the clubhouse turn, chased off the rail at the back in the middle stages, angled back to the rail on the far turn, tipped three wide past the quarter pole, kept on trying through the lane but could not get by OAKHURST for third. REBEL GIRL closest in pursuit in the two path, raced up close from outside in the middle stages, challenged the winner around the far turn, failed to kick on with that rival at the top of the lane and flattened in the late stages. LUMINIFEROUS raced in range in the three path, came four wide into the drive and weakened.
